Etymology[edit]

From altus +‎ -iō.

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ˈal.ti.oː/, [ˈaɫ̪.t̪i.oː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ˈal.t͡si.o/, [ˈal.t͡si.ɔ]
  • (Vulgar) IPA(key): /ˈal.ti.oː/, [ˈal.tʲ.o]

Verb[edit]

altiō (present infinitive altiāre, perfect active altiāvī, supine altiātum); first conjugation

  1. (Medieval Latin) I raise, elevate
  2. (Medieval Latin) I erect, build up
